-- Correct: Manitoba Says Hog Exports to U.S. Dropped 77%
-- B y   J e n   S k e r r i t t
-- 2013-05-24T21:24:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-24/correct-manitoba-says-hog-exports-to-u-s-dropped-77-.html
(Corrects attribution in the lead.)  The decline was between 2007 and
2012, Entrepreneurship, Training and Trade Minister Peter
Bjornson said in an e-mailed statement.
* Tighter country-of-origin label rules imposed by the U.S. will
further discriminate against Manitoba’s cattle and hog producers
and “worsen the barriers facing Canadian livestock,”
Agriculture Minister Ron Kostyshyn said in the statement
* NOTE: Since 2009, the U.S. has required food processors to
identify the nations where cattle, hogs and some fresh produce
originate
* NOTE: The  U.S. Department of Agriculture  said yesterday it
will tighten rules so labels specify where animals are born,
raised and slaughtered  To contact the reporter on this story:
